Available now — $950/month

Hey there! I’m a graduating Georgia Tech master’s student looking for a sublease in Atlanta until mid or end of September. I’m very clean and responsible.

If you’re looking for someone to take over your lease for the summer or know anyone with a place available, please feel free to message me!

***Price Reduction***
***One Year minimum lease***
***Serious inquiry only***

Lease a furnished room in a one-floor house a few blocks from Georgia Tech and Atlantic Station with plenty of street permit parking. The private furnished room and bathroom are equipped with central AC, heat, private entrance, hardwood floors, and central heating. You'll also have access to the house's high-speed wifi.  All utilities and lawn services are included.  You'll have access to the furnished, common area with a renovated kitchen, complete with granite countertops and a new, stainless steel range. You'll also have access to a new washer/dryer, porch, and yard. There's also a shared driveway.  The house is a peaceful, quiet home in the heart of Atlanta. Note: We have our own section in the house, though we don't live there. We visit about 4-6 times a year, staying in our designated area and sharing a bathroom.

****Rooms will be available on August 1st, 2025.***
Leasing starts now.

Rent +utilities ($1,1977.00 per month for this Room)

Hello again!

We have exciting news for students interested in our room for rent at 633 Parsons St SW for the 2025-2026 school year!

For a limited time, you can get **$100 off your first month's rent**! This means your first month will be just $1000, with subsequent months at the usual $1100 (inclusive of utilities).

Don't miss out on this offer! If you're interested, you can find more details and apply through this TurboTenant link:[https://rental.turbotenant.com/p/633-parsons-st-sw-atlanta-ga/1627542](https://rental.turbotenant.com/p/633-parsons-st-sw-atlanta-ga/1627542)

Riverfront Room Available – 12 Minutes from Buckhead, 4 Minutes from Cumberland Mall 🌿

• $865/month – all bills included

We’re looking for one more roommate to join our 3-bedroom, 2-bathroom apartment starting August 1st or August 15th.

Enjoy living surrounded by nature with a scenic trail that runs along the Chattahoochee River—perfect for walking or jogging. The apartment is located in a quiet and green community with great amenities:

🏞️ Highlights:
 • River access and nature trail
 • 12 minutes from Buckhead
 • 4 minutes from Cumberland Mall
 • 2 swimming pools
 • Tennis court
 • Gym

You’d be sharing the apartment with two clean, respectful roommates who work full-time and are rarely home.

11x12 room with shard bathroom for rent in an airy **shared 3b/2b** on a quiet street in Oakland City. Generally 12-15 minute drive to GT campus, though can be ~30 mins if you’re going right at rush hour. **850$ + electricity.** O**ptionally furnished with queen mattress (avocado brand).  **Wifi, monthly cleaning service, yard maintenance, and other utilities are included. Onsite laundry and dishwasher, deck, porch, fenced in back yard with fire pit. Street parking in front of the house.

Roommates are a gay 25M moving in from DC for his masters at GT, a straight 30F who is a software engineer, and an orange cat. We (the humans) both WFH, and like cooking, gardening, rock climbing, and keeping a nice home. There's a massive organic garden in the front yard, you’re welcome to gardening and to excess veggies when it’s harvesting time. Cannot accommodate other pets. No smoking inside the house, but you’re welcome to do so on the porch/outside. Must be LGBTQ+ friendly.

3 min drive to Kroger, 6 mins to Westside Beltline, Lee & White. 8 min bike to the Oakland City Marta. Great bouldering and muai thai gyms nearby. ~20 min drive to midtown depending on traffic.

We’d love to co-habitate with a 3rd person who is respectful, clean, values direct communication and likes doing their own thing, who's down to socialize with the people they live with on occasion if we all get along. If you’re like a 7- 8 /10 on the cleanliness scale, and would be up for activities like grilling/board games/a casual drink with housemates every now and then if we vibe, we’ll be a good fit! Also very happy to just have a chill roommate who is drama free.
 

If you’re interested, shoot me a DM letting me know a bit about yourself, how long you’re looking to stay, and your situation.

Hi! I am looking for a fully furnished studio or 1 bed unit from August 1 - October 31st. I’m also open to finding an existing roommate situation.

Feel free to message me or comment on post. Thank you!
